I, Charlotte Porter, am pleading guilty to the charge of careless driving. I accept full responsibility for my actions on the day in question. I want to express my deepest remorse and regret for the careless and dangerous choices I made that day.

On my way to the airport to pick up my family members, I was running late and allowed my impatience to cloud my judgment. I drove aggressively and at a speed exceeding the limit, which ultimately led to me crashing into a guardrail. Thankfully, no one else was harmed as a result of my reckless behavior.

I am aware that my license already carries 3 penalty points for a previous speeding offense. This indicates that I need to learn from my past mistakes. It is clear that my actions on that day were not only irresponsible but also posed a significant risk to the safety of others on the road.

In hindsight, I have realized how dangerous my actions on this day were, and I deeply regret them. I know I could have caused harm not only to myself but to everyone around me on the road as well.

Your Honor, I stand before you today, openly acknowledging my guilt and accepting the consequences of my actions.

